In other to control traffic, both human and vehicular, as well provide security of lives and property in Abuja City Center, during the All Progressive Congress (APC) National Convention scheduled to hold from 25th to 27th March 2022 at the Eagle Square Abuja. The Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Police Command has deployed more personnel to be on hand. A statement made available to pressmen in Abuja via the FCT Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Josephine Adeh, stated that, “The convention is usually greeted with a heavy influx of the Politicos from every part of the country and will be graced by the attendance of The President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, President Muhammadu Buhari(GCFR), The Vice president, and other notable party stakeholders. “In the light of the above, and in other to ensure maximum safety as well as the continuation of economic activities which largely depends on road traffic, the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Police Command after critically and considerably drafting an operational order to maximize the deployment of human and material resources for the success of the convention, have deemed it fit intimate members of the public about a few traffic diversions as follows; 1. Good luck Ebele Jonathan By the court of appeal
